com.storytron.swat.loglizard

Class LogTreeModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.storytron.swat.loglizard.LogTreeModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.tree.TreeModel

    public final class LogTreeModel
extends java.lang.Object
implements javax.swing.tree.TreeModel, java.io.Serializable
    A tree model that manages a big log tree. It uses disk storage to decrease memory requirements.

    Currently there are two threads that use the methods in this class.

    • The event dispatcher thread uses the TreeModel interface methods and the constructor.
    • All the other methods are used by the log processor thread.
    See Also:

      • streams

        public final java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,TreeOutputStream> streams
        Streams of branches being written. The key is the index of a root child whose descendants are being written. The stored value is a stream used to write there.

        The streams in this map satisfy the invariant that their cursors are inside of some branch (i.e. not in between of two consecutive branches).
